#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Addon Features:"
msgstr "Caratteristiche principali:"

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid "Speech support:"
msgstr "accesso in sintesi vocale:"

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Dialogs and menus are properly reported;"
msgstr "Vocalizza correttamente le finestre di dialogo ed i menù;"

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Natural speech support for math formulas using the Lambda math engine, i.e. "
"\"compound root 3 sep compound root 3 x plus 24, close compound root, minus 3 "
"equals 0\";"
msgstr ""
"Vocalizza le formule matematiche utilizzando il sistema di processamento di "
"testi di LAMBDA, quindi legge correttamente ed in modo naturale il testo "
"matematico (ad esempio \"radice 3 di 3x più 24, fine radice\");"

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "implemented the Reading by character, words, lines and Say All;"
msgstr "Permette di leggere per carattere, riga, o con il leggi-tutto;"

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Speaks when a block of text is selected or extended (using CTRL+B and SHIFT"
"+CTRL+B);"
msgstr ""
"Vocalizza correttamente la selezione dei blocchi, usando ctrl-b o shift-ctrl-"
"b;"

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Speaks when moving in the text editor using standard Windows commands and "
"Lambda-specific commands;"
msgstr ""
"Vocalizza correttamente gli spostamenti all'interno del testo utilizzando i "
"principali tasti standard di Windows e quelli specifici di LAMBDA;"

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Both Extended and Short speech modes are supported (you can select it using "
"the Tools menu in Lambda);"
msgstr ""
"Vocalizza sia in maniera compatta che estesa, funzione modificabile dal menu "
"strumenti di Lambda;"

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Special dialogs like structure mode, calculator, and matrix window are now "
"correctly reported and NVDA reads correctly when moving the cursor around or "
"when new text is typed ;"
msgstr ""
"Vocalizza le finestre di esplorazione struttura, la calcolatrice e la "
"finestra di esplorazione delle matrici;"

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Typing echo uses the Lambda text processor, so symbols and markers will be "
"correctly reported."
msgstr ""
"Il riscontro in scrittura avviene usando il sistema di processamento testi di "
"LAMBDA, di modo da annunciare correttamente i simboli e i marcatori."

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid "Braille support:"
msgstr "Supporto Braille:"

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"The addon installs (inside the user profile directory) and activates a custom "
"braille table. This table may be different for different languages. Custom "
"braille tables were made from ones in the Lambda plugin for JAWS (jbt file). "
"Then symbols and markers are represented using the same dots patterns;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"The addon creates an NVDA profile for a standard braille configuration. By "
"this, the output is set to the custom braille table only when the Lambda "
"application is active;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "Dialogs and menus are properly reported in braille;"
msgstr ""
"Le finestre di dialogo e i menu vengono mostrati in braille in maniera "
"appropriata;"

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"The content of the editor is correctly rendered in braille and the user is "
"able to move using braille scrolling keys or cursor routing keys;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Starting from the addon version 1.1.0, there are two ways in which the text "
"in the Lambda editor is rendered: \"Flat mode\" and \"non-Flat Mode\". When "
"the \"Flat mode\" is on, NVDA will use the Display Model to retrieve "
"information from the editor and to determine the caret position. This is "
"specially beneficial when the user needs to move around on the screen, even "
"in white spaces. When the \"Flat Mode\" is set to \"off\", text rendering on "
"the braille display is more stable, since NVDA uses Windows API to retrieve "
"it. However when the the caret is moved in white spaces next to the end of "
"the line of text, the braille display does not follow the real cursor as long "
"as a non-white space is added by the user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The \"flat mode\" is active by default. You can toggle \"flat mode\" on or "
"off by pressing NVDA+SHIFT+F."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"We strongly recommend to disable the Flat Mode if you are using custom DPI in "
"Windows (Custom sizing option), especially when you have screen settings with "
"more than 96 dpi (larger than 100%)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"The structure of dialog boxes is easier, repeated information has been "
"removed;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"The selection will be marked properly using dots 7 and 8, and marking is "
"properly refreshed while standard Windows commands (SHIFT+ARROWS) or Lambda "
"specific commands (CTRL+B, CTRL+SHIFT+B) are pressed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Before starting to use this addon."
msgstr "Prima di iniziare ad utilizzare questo componente aggiuntivo."

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"This addon creates an NVDA profile named \"lambda\" which is associated with "
"the \"lambda.exe\" application. The profile automatically sets all braille "
"options: the custom braille table, the focus tethering and flat mode settings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"If a previous profile with the same name is present in your system, the addon "
"will not override it and you have to manually adjust your configuration "
"profile."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"To stave off this situation, if you have specific settings you'd like to "
"preserve, you can use the \"Revert LAMBDA Profile Wizard\". The shortcut to "
"start this tool is NVDA+alt+r (when focused in LAMBDA)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"An easy option is also to delete old versions of the \"lambda\" profile after "
"the installation of the addon. To do so, open the NVDA menu, select the "
"\"Configuration profiles\" menu Item and press ENTER."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"In the Configuration profiles dialog, you'll be able to locate and delete the "
"\"lambda\" profile. The profile will be re-created the next time the Lambda "
"application is started."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Deleting the \"lambda\" profile should be an easy solution also when the "
"addon runs into any problem. For instance, if the braille table is not "
"properly set, instead of manually configuring the profile, you can simply "
"delete it. The addon will create a new one the next time you'll load the "
"Lambda editor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Each time the Lambda editor is started, this addon checks if a profile with "
"the name \"lambda\" exists. If it doesn't, it automatically generates a "
"profile with the following form:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "``` filename : userData\\profiles\\lambda.ini :"
msgstr "``` filename : userData\\profiles\\lambda.ini :"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[braille]\n"
"\treadByParagraph = False\n"
"\ttetherTo = focus\n"
"\ttranslationTable = path-to-the-addon-brailleTable-dir\\tableName\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[lambda]\n"
"\tbrailleFlatMode = True\n"
msgstr ""
"[lambda]\n"
"\tbrailleFlatMode = True\n"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "```"
msgstr "```"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Where :"
msgstr "Dove :"

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"path-to-the-addon-brailleTable-dir : is the absolute path of the addon "
"directory + \"\\brailleTables\""
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"tableName : depends on the active NVDA language. Currently only the italian "
"and Spanish braille tables, \"lambda-ita.utb\" and \"lambda-esp.utb\" "
"respectively, is present."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Addon Keyboard Shortcuts:"
msgstr "Comandi rapidi da tastiera per il componente:"

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "**NVDA+Shift+f**: Toggle braille flat mode on or off;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "**NVDA+alt+r**: Open the \"Revert LAMBDA Profile Wizard\";"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "**NVDA+d**: Duplicate lines (use this instad of control+d)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Known issues:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Due to a bug present in LAMBDA, the add-on provides an extra-logic that "
"reports white spaces. This logic may fail in the following situations:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"When words like \"space\", \"spazio\" \"Espacio\" etc. are inserted into the "
"text, they may be reported by NVDA as the local NVDA language translation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Blank lines are not reported by the LAMBDA speech engine. The user will hear "
"the translation of the word \"space\" instead. This could be both a blank "
"line or a line containing only the word \"space\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Useful tips"
msgstr "Suggerimenti utili"

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"This is a set of tips that will help you on using the addon in a more "
"eficient way."
msgstr ""
"Questo è un insieme di consigli che aiuterà ad utilizzare il componente in "
"maniera più efficiente."

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid ""
"Character-by-character reporting: Normally, when working with maths you would "
"like NVDA to report things you're writing character by character. To do this, "
"there are a couple of simple steps: ensure to have the focus on the LAMBDA's "
"window or one of its variants (the six dots representation, for example); "
"press NVDA+2 (number two) or navigate to NVDA menu>Preferences>Keyboard "
"settings and check the box to Speak typed characters; go to "
"LAMBDA>Options>Voice paramethers and ensure the checkbox \"echo\" is ON, "
"otherwhise NVDA won't receive anything from the speech engine while you are "
"typing. And done, NVDA will speak written characters, but don't worry, only "
"in LAMBDA or its special windows, the settings for the rest of applications "
"will be left as they were."
msgstr ""

